Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of digital ink data, which is often used in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The categorisation and implementation of features also involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the use case of analysing cognitive assessments performed using a digital pen could fall under the category of cyberpsychology (cs.CY).
